content, which is worth noting as the primary finding. The property list in the usage section covers sender specification, initialization parameters, hook arrays, and call ordering—all of which are represented in the knowledge file's property table, so coverage is complete. I'm noticing one potential indexing issue: the first section combines both \"概要\" and \"要求\" content but is only labeled as \"概要\" in the index, though the hints do capture key terms from both sections so retrieval should still work. The main finding is just this minor section count discrepancy between the source and knowledge file.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":19346,"cache_read_input_tokens":18561,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":19346,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"61589c43-4773-48be-bdad-05e9147c483f","uuid":"7bb8c71c-d4d1-4256-9678-8bb92e39cc26"}
